# Practical 5: Deploying a Static Website on AWS S3

## Objective

To host a static website using AWS S3 by configuring bucket permissions and enabling static website hosting.

## Steps

1. Log in to the AWS Management Console.

2. Search for S3 in the top search bar and open the S3 Dashboard.

3. Click on “Create Bucket”.

   * Enter a unique bucket name
   * Select a region
   * Uncheck “Block all public access” and acknowledge

4. Open the created bucket and upload website files (e.g., index.html).

5. Make the uploaded files public.

6. Go to the Properties tab and enable “Static Website Hosting”.

   * Set index document as index.html

7. Go to Permissions and add a bucket policy to allow public read access.

8. Copy the bucket website endpoint URL and open it in a browser.

## Code (index.html)

<html>  
  <head><title>My Website</title></head>  
  <body>  
    <h1>Hello World</h1>  
    <p>This is my static website hosted on AWS S3.</p>  
  </body>  
</html>  

## Result

The static website was successfully deployed using AWS S3 and accessed through the website endpoint URL.
